meta {
  name: VOZVRAT (REVERSAL)
  type: http
  seq: 4
}

post {
  url: {{url}}
  body: json
  auth: inherit
}

body:json {
  {
    "task": "reversal",
    "data": {
      "amount": 0.5,
      "tagRRN": "123"
    }
  }
}

settings {
  encodeUrl: true
  timeout: 0
}

docs {
  The task field must fill with value.
  The value of the amount field is an option. If the value did not fill with any number,
  represents a whole reversal transaction. If the value has been filled with specific
  numbers, represent part reversal. The POS terminal controls whether support part
  reversal transaction or not. There is a switch within PSP
  (Settings->Admin->Common->Partial Cancellation Support), enable this switch to
  support partial reversal, otherwise no support.
  ```
  {
    “task”:”reversal”,
    “data”:{
      “amount”:String(option)
      “tagRRN”:String(got from the RRN of original transactions, Mandatory)
    }
  }
  
  4.5.2 Response
  {
    "data": {
      "cardNo": String, //card PAN,the format example: "100007******8909
      "issuerName": String, //card type
      "tagRRN": String,
      "msg":String,
      "result": int, // 0 indicates success or failure
      "receiptInfo":String,
      “channel”:int //0:other bank card 1:jusan bank card
    }
  }
  ```
  PAX Technology 13
  Example:
  ```
  request:
  {
    "task":"reversal",
    "data":{
      "tagRRN":"311887318045",
      "amount":"113"
    }
  }
  
  response:
  {
    "data": {
      "cardNo": "100006******5200",
      "channel": 0,
      "issuerName": "VISA",
      "receiptInfo": "ТОО \"Cullinan\"\nг
      . Алматы, ул. Мака
      т а е в а , 127/1\n И И Н 201240002166\n т е л : +7 777 77
      77\n------------------------------------------------\nCustomer Check 0002\nRRN:
      311887318045\n------------------------------------------------\nUniReversal\n(Purchase)
      17:36 28/04/2023\nTerminal ID: 05899991\nCard NO.: 1000********5200\nExpiry:
      12/44\nType: VISA\nAmount: -113₸\n00:Successfully completed\n",
      "tagRRN": "311887318045",
      "msg": "Operation is Successful",
      "result": 0
    }
  }
  ```
}
